<p class="p">The treatment of organic waste by 
 <italic class="italic">H. illucens</italic> larvae is gaining attention [
 <xref rid="B69-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">69</xref>,
 <xref rid="B110-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">110</xref>,
 <xref rid="B132-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">132</xref>,
 <xref rid="B133-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">133</xref>,
 <xref rid="B134-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">134</xref>,
 <xref rid="B135-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">135</xref>]. In addition, other types of waste are being explored as potential substrates for the sustainable use of 
 <italic class="italic">H. illucens</italic> larvae biomass as food for humans and other animals [
 <xref rid="B43-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">43</xref>,
 <xref rid="B136-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">136</xref>,
 <xref rid="B137-animals-09-00349" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">137</xref>].
</p>
